<div class="comments-body">
<p>Thanks for the kinds words!</p>

<p>As the author of this, I can tell you that, yes, it's written in Direct3D. We used the managed code interfaces to Direct3D in C# to do this. </p>

<p>I also wish that the AI for face recognition was better. We DO use face detection code (from MSR Asia) to detect pictures with faces in them, but that's still a long way from face recognition.</p>

<p>BTW, you can check out a longer video from the CES conference on my homepage:  http://www.research.microsoft.com/~sdrucker/Video/nextMediaCES.wmv</p>

<p>We're also looking at ways to do similar work ontop of Avalon.<br />
Cheers!<br />
--Steve</p>
